  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH Assistance to Vulnerable Returnees and Host Families Affected by Post-election Violence in Western C&#xF4;te d&#x2019;Ivoire</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	80% of beneficiary households can cite at least three (3) ways to reduce their risk of contracting WASH related diseases
&#x2022;	400 women and men (5 persons per village) and 20 women and men (5 persons per NGO) are trained in water quality treatment/monitoring and hygiene promotion
&#x2022;	160 community water point and sanitation management committees (consisting of women and men members) receive pertinent water points management and hygiene promotion training
&#x2022;	UNICEF fulfils its role as WASH cluster lead through efficient information management and information sharing

All the above indicators are to be achieved within six (6) months of the receipt of funding.</narrative>
  </description>
